                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d793">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/883: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-11T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 11, 1938—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>200. Your 601, November 8, 6 p.m. You may wish to take a suitable occasion
                    informally to advise Weizsaecker that it will be exceedingly difficult for the
                    Committee to make progress in arranging for the settlement elsewhere of
                    substantial numbers of refugees until such time as arrangements can be made for
                    each emigrant to take with him a minimum amount of capital sufficient at least
                    to cover his establishment in the country of settlement and his integration into
                    a new economy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
